␺R ϭ 2e 4␲␧0␧rr ,

[7]

where ⌿R ϭ 0.58*⌬V1/2, ⌬V1/2 is the the Qo-V shift (Ϫ24 mV; Fig. 3 f and g ), e is the elementary charge, ␧r is the dielectric constant of water, ␧0 is the permittivity of free space, and 1/␬ (8.07 Å) is the
Debye length in the aqueous phase and is calculated as in ref. 26.

Structural Model. The structure of Mg2ϩ binding site of the mSlo1 channel was generated based on the crystal structure of the MthK channel by using the PyMol molecular graphics system (www. pymol.org).

